    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow vulnerability in ue_supported_dl_layers function\n\n### Summary\nThe NR gNB RRC configuration contained a buffer overflow vulnerability in the `set_dl_maxmimolayers` function when processing UE capability information. The vulnerability occurred when the UE reported invalid `maxNumberMIMO_LayersPDSCH` values that were outside the expected range defined in the 3GPP specification.\n\nThe issue was caused by missing bounds checking on the `maxNumberMIMO_LayersPDSCH` enumeration value before using it in bit shift operations. According to 3GPP TS 38.331, this field should only contain values 0-2 (representing twoLayers, fourLayers, eightLayers), but the code did not validate this before processing.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/nr_rrc_config.c`: Added bounds checking for `ue_supported_layers_enum` to prevent buffer overflow when the value is outside the valid range [0,2]\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/nr_rrc_config.c`: Added bounds checking for the `maxMIMO_layers` parameter to ensure it's within reasonable limits [1,8]\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/nr_rrc_config.c`: Added proper error logging to help with debugging when invalid values are encountered\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/nr_rrc_config.c`: Added missing LOG header include to support the logging functionality\n\nUnder certain network conditions with malformed UE capability reports, this could lead to incorrect memory access patterns and potential crashes in the RRC configuration processing path.\n"
}